GUI tools for information gathering of hardware in linux:

**************************************
  i-nex:
it is a system and hardware Information tool for Linux. I-Nex is a tool that collect information for hardware components available on  system and show it using a user interface.it written in gambas3, python, bash.
 
install Dependencies:
sudo apt-get install debhelper devscripts pkg-config dpkg-dev lsb-release gambas3-dev gambas3-gb-image gambas3-gb-qt5 gambas3-gb-form gambas3-gb-desktop gambas3-gb-form-stock git

install in Ubuntu:
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:gambas-team/gambas3 && \
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:i-nex-development-team/stable && \
sudo apt-get update

Install from repository:
sudo apt install i-nex

Install RPM from repository:
dnf install i-nex i-nex-data

install in arch base:
sudo pacman -S i-nex libcpuid


website:
http://i-nex.linux.pl
**************************************
  
  
 	   hardinfo:
system information and benchmark tool in Linux. It can generate a full statistics on system. 
Also, Displays a list of devices:
Operating System details, Kernel Module, Boot infoâ€™s, Languages, File system details, Users.
Processor Info, Memory info, PCI devices, USB devices, Printer details, Battery Info, Sensors.
Interfaces, IP Connections, Routing Table, ARP Table, Share Directories, DNS Servers.
CPU Blowfish, CPU Cryptohash, CPU, Fibonacci, CPU N-Queens, FPU FFT.
  
  Required:
    GTK+ 2.10 (or newer)
    GLib 2.10 (or newer)
    Zlib (for zlib benchmark)

install in ubuntu:
sudo apt update 
sudo apt install hardinfo

run from terminal:
$ hardinfo

https://pkgs.org/download/hardinfo
